## Ticket & Deliverable

**Goal:** Add user authentication to the application with login and logout functionality.

**Human-verifiable deliverable:** Users can log in via a login form, see their authenticated state in the UI, and log out via a logout button. Authentication state persists across page refreshes.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] AC1: Login form accepts email and password, validates input, and authenticates user
- [ ] AC2: Authenticated users see their username/email displayed in the UI header
- [ ] AC3: Logout button is visible when user is authenticated and logs user out on click
- [ ] AC4: Authentication state persists across page refreshes (stored in localStorage or sessionStorage)
- [ ] AC5: Unauthenticated users are redirected to login page when accessing protected routes

